<h3>"Movie Theater" Popcorn</h3>
<br>
<img src="movie pop.jfif" class="img-rounded" alt="Popcorn2" width="500" height="400">
<br>
  <div class="container">
  <p style= font-size:150%> Movie theaters use butter-flavored oil, which has a lower water content than butter so it makes popcorn less soggy. Real clarified butter has the same effect.
   <br>
   Microwave melt 1 stick of butter 
   <br>
   Wait 5 min then remove top layer of foam on butter and any unmelted chunks
   <br>
   For every tablespoon of butter, use 5 cups of popcorn (add salt sparingly)
   </p>
   <br>
